🏅 MODEL INTERPRETATION

Stability Drivers (Positive Influences on Stability):
├─ Low birth/fertility rates (demographic stability)
├─ Strong education systems (human capital)
├─ High GDP per capita (economic prosperity)
├─ Low population pressure (resource adequacy)
└─ Accessible healthcare infrastructure

Stability Threats (Risk Indicators):
├─ High birth/fertility rates (population growth pressure)
├─ Weak education pipelines (skill gaps)
├─ Low GDP per capita (economic hardship)
├─ High dependency ratios (working-age burden)
├─ High fuel costs (economic stress)
└─ Environmental pressure (sustainability concerns)


